{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853608515,"sessionID":"ses_286e0a496ffeAx3bF2slH4epid","part":{"id":"prt_d791f92c3001nMJaky3KFKGRDb","messageID":"msg_d791f7bda001swX0MnXMBxE0nW","sessionID":"ses_286e0a496ffeAx3bF2slH4epid","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-bc2bb1d82a004d7e86faf446c24ac774","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/router` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Core Data Structures (ST-1) ✓\n18: \n19: - [x] **T1.1**: Define JWT constants in `jwt.go`\n20:   - `rsaKeySize = 2048`\n21:   - `jwtExpiration = 5 * time.Minute`\n22:   - `IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"`\n23:   - `PrivateKeyDataKey = \"private.pem\"`\n24:   - `PublicKeyDataKey = \"public.pem\"`\n25:   - `IdentityNamespace = \"default\"` (overridden by `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env)\n26:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n27:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerTokenExpiration -v`\n28: \n29: - [x] **T1.2**: Define `JWTManager` struct in `jwt.go`\n30:   - `privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey`\n31:   - `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey`\n32:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n33:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewJWTManager -v`\n34: \n35: - [x] **T1.3**: Define `JWTSigningError` in `errors.go`\n36:   - `Err error` field\n37:   - Implements `APIStatus` interface\n38:   - `Status() = 500`, `Code() = \"JWT_SIGNING_FAILED\"`\n39:   - File: `pkg/router/errors.go`\n40:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTSigningError -v`\n41: \n42: ### Phase 2: JWT Generation (ST-2) ✓\n43: \n44: - [x] **T2.1**: Implement `NewJWTManager()` constructor\n45:   - Generate RSA 2048-bit key: `rsa.GenerateKey(rand.Reader, 2048)`\n46:   - Derive public key from private key\n47:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n48:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewJWTManager -v`\n49: \n50: - [x] **T2.2**: Implement `GenerateToken(claims)` method\n51:   - Create JWT with standard claims: `exp` (now+5m), `iat` (now), `iss=\"agentcube-router\"`\n52:   - Merge custom claims into `jwt.MapClaims`\n53:   - Sign with RS256 algorithm\n54:   - Return signed token string or `JWTSigningError`\n55:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n56:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerGenerateToken -v`\n57: \n58: - [x] **T2.3**: Implement PEM encoding helpers\n59:   - `encodePrivateKeyPEM(key)` - PKCS1 PEM encoding with \"RSA PRIVATE KEY\" block\n60:   - `encodePublicKeyPEM(key)` - PKIX PEM encoding with \"PUBLIC KEY\" block\n61:   - `loadPrivateKeyPEM(data)` - Parse PKCS1 PEM back to `*rsa.PrivateKey`\n62:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n63:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestEncodePrivateKeyPEM -v`\n64: \n65: - [x] **T2.4**: Implement `GetPublicKey()` method\n66:   - Return `*rsa.PublicKey` for downstream verification\n67:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n68:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerGetPublicKey -v`\n69: \n70: - [x] **T2.5**: Implement `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)` placeholder\n71:   - Log warning \"not in cluster, skipping secret persistence\"\n72:   - Return nil (placeholder for future K8s Secret persistence)\n73:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n74:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n75: \n76: ### Phase 3: JWT Verification (ST-3)\n77: \n78: - [ ] **T3.1**: Define `RouterClaims` struct\n79:   - Extend `jwt.RegisteredClaims`\n80:   - Custom fields: `SessionID string`, `SandboxID string`, `Namespace string`, `Name string`\n81:   - JSON tags: `session_id`, `sandbox_id`, `namespace`, `name`\n82:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n83:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n84: \n85: - [ ] **T3.2**: Define additional JWT error types in `errors.go`\n86:   - `JWTValidationError` - code `JWT_VALIDATION_FAILED`, HTTP 401\n87:   - `JWTTokenExpiredError` - code `JWT_TOKEN_EXPIRED`, HTTP 401, field `TokenID`\n88:   - `JWTTokenMissingError` - code `JWT_TOKEN_MISSING`, HTTP 401\n89:   - `JWTInvalidFormatError` - code `JWT_INVALID_FORMAT`, HTTP 401\n90:   - `JWTKeyLoadError` - code `JWT_KEY_LOAD_FAILED`, HTTP 500\n91:   - All implement `APIStatus` interface\n92:   - File: `pkg/router/errors.go`\n93:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTError -v`\n94: \n95: - [ ] **T3.3**: Implement `ValidateToken(tokenString)` method\n96:   - Parse token with public key verification\n97:   - Map jwt library errors to custom error types\n98:   - Return `*RouterClaims` on success\n99:   - Handle: `jwt.ErrTokenExpired` → `JWTTokenExpiredError`\n100:   - Handle: `jwt.ErrTokenSignatureInvalid` → `JWTValidationError`\n101:   - Handle: `jwt.ErrTokenMalformed` → `JWTValidationError`\n102:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n103:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerValidateToken -v`\n104: \n105: - [ ] **T3.4**: Implement JWT error mapping helper\n106:   - `mapJWTParseError(err)` function\n107:   - Convert `jwt` library errors to router custom errors\n108:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n109:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestMapJWTParseError -v`\n110: \n111: ### Phase 4: Authentication Middleware (ST-4)\n112: \n113: - [ ] **T4.1**: Define `JWTAuthMiddlewareConfig` struct\n114:   - `SkipPaths []string` - paths to bypass auth (e.g., `/health/*`)\n115:   - `TokenExtractor TokenExtractor` - custom token extraction function\n116:   - `KeyFunc jwt.Keyfunc` - key lookup function\n117:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n118:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T4.2**: Define `TokenExtractor` function type\n121:   - `type TokenExtractor func(r *http.Request) (string, error)`\n122:   - Extract token from Authorization header or other sources\n123:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n124:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n125: \n126: - [ ] **T4.3**: Implement `DefaultTokenExtractor(r)` function\n127:   - Get `Authorization` header from request\n128:   - Split by space, check format is \"Bearer <token>\"\n129:   - Return token string or `JWTTokenMissingError`/`JWTInvalidFormatError`\n130:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n131:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestDefaultTokenExtractor -v`\n132: \n133: - [ ] **T4.4**: Implement `JWTAuthMiddleware(jwtMgr, config)` function\n134:   - Create Gin middleware for JWT verification\n135:   - Skip paths matching `config.SkipPaths`\n136:   - Extract token via `config.TokenExtractor` or `DefaultTokenExtractor`\n137:   - Validate token via `jwtMgr.ValidateToken`\n138:   - Inject claims into `gin.Context` via `c.Set(\"jwt_claims\", claims)`\n139:   - Return appropriate error response on validation failure\n140:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n141:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTAuthMiddleware -v`\n142: \n143: - [ ] **T4.5**: Implement error response formatting in middleware\n144:   - Use `APIStatus` interface for error details\n145:   - Return JSON: `{\"error\": \"<message>\", \"code\": \"<code>\"}`\n146:   - Set HTTP status code from `Status()` method\n147:   - Call `c.Abort()` to stop request processing\n148:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n149:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTAuthMiddlewareErrors -v`\n150: \n151: - [ ] **T4.6**: Implement claims extraction helper `GetClaimsFromContext(c)`\n152:   - Retrieve claims from `gin.Context` via `c.Get(\"jwt_claims\")`\n153:   - Return `*RouterClaims` or nil if not present\n154:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware.go`\n155:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestGetClaimsFromContext -v`\n156: \n157: ### Phase 5: Key Persistence (ST-5)\n158: \n159: - [ ] **T5.1**: Define `KeySecret` struct\n160:   - `Name string` - Secret name: `\"picod-router-identity\"`\n161:   - `Namespace string` - From `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE`\n162:   - `Data map[string][]byte` - Keys: `\"private.pem\"` and `\"public.pem\"`\n163:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n164:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n165: \n166: - [ ] **T5.2**: Implement `KeyManager` struct\n167:   - `k8sClient kubernetes.Interface`\n168:   - `namespace string`\n169:   - `secretName string`\n170:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n171:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n172: \n173: - [ ] **T5.3**: Implement `NewKeyManager(k8sClient)` constructor\n174:   - Read namespace from `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` env or default to `\"default\"`\n175:   - Set `secretName = IdentitySecretName`\n176:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n177:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewKeyManager -v`\n178: \n179: - [ ] **T5.4**: Implement `KeyManager.Exists(ctx)` method\n180:   - Check if Kubernetes Secret exists\n181:   - Call `k8sClient.CoreV1().Secrets(namespace).Get(ctx, name, options)`\n182:   - Return `true` if exists, `false` if `IsNotFound` error\n183:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n184:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManagerExists -v`\n185: \n186: - [ ] **T5.5**: Implement `KeyManager.Load(ctx)` method\n187:   - Get Secret from Kubernetes\n188:   - Parse `secret.Data[\"private.pem\"]` via `loadPrivateKeyPEM`\n189:   - Return `*rsa.PrivateKey` or `JWTKeyLoadError`\n190:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n191:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManagerLoad -v`\n192: \n193: - [ ] **T5.6**: Implement `KeyManager.Store(ctx, privateKey)` method\n194:   - Encode private key via `encodePrivateKeyPEM`\n195:   - Encode public key via `encodePublicKeyPEM`\n196:   - Create Kubernetes Secret with `Data` map\n197:   - Call `k8sClient.CoreV1().Secrets(namespace).Create(ctx, secret, options)`\n198:   - Return error on failure\n199:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n200:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManagerStore -v`\n201: \n202: - [ ] **T5.7**: Update `JWTManager.TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)` implementation\n203:   - Check if `k8sClient` is nil → skip (not in cluster)\n204:   - Call `KeyManager.Exists(ctx)`\n205:   - If exists: `KeyManager.Load(ctx)` → set private/public key\n206:   - If not exists: `KeyManager.Store(ctx, privateKey)` → persist new keys\n207:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n208:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerKeyPersistence -v`\n209: \n210: ### Phase 6: JWT Config (Optional) (ST-6)\n211: \n212: - [ ] **T6.1**: Define `JWTConfig` struct\n213:   - `Algorithm string` - default `\"RS256\"`, optional `\"HS256\"`\n214:   - `TokenExpiry time.Duration` - default `5 * time.Minute`\n215:   - `RefreshExpiry time.Duration` - default `30 * time.Minute`\n216:   - `Issuer string` - default `\"agentcube-router\"`\n217:   - `Audience []string` - optional\n218:   - `ClockSkew time.Duration` - default `30s`\n219:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n220:   - Verification: `go build ./pkg/router/...`\n221: \n222: - [ ] **T6.2**: Implement `DefaultJWTConfig()` function\n223:   - Return config with default values\n224:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n225:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestDefaultJWTConfig -v`\n226: \n227: - [ ] **T6.3**: Update `NewJWTManager()` to accept optional `JWTConfig`\n228:   - `NewJWTManager(config *JWTConfig)` - nil config uses defaults\n229:   - Use config values for token expiration and issuer\n230:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt.go`\n231:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerWithConfig -v`\n232: \n233: ### Phase 7: Unit Tests (ST-7)\n234: \n235: - [ ] **T7.1**: Add `ValidateToken` tests in `jwt_test.go`\n236:   - Test valid token verification\n237:   - Test expired token → `JWTTokenExpiredError`\n238:   - Test invalid signature → `JWTValidationError`\n239:   - Test malformed token → `JWTValidationError`\n240:   - Test token with custom claims extraction\n241:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n242:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerValidateToken -v`\n243: \n244: - [ ] **T7.2**: Add JWT error type tests in `errors_test.go`\n245:   - Test `JWTValidationError` implements `APIStatus`\n246:   - Test `JWTTokenExpiredError` implements `APIStatus`\n247:   - Test `JWTTokenMissingError` implements `APIStatus`\n248:   - Test `JWTInvalidFormatError` implements `APIStatus`\n249:   - Test `JWTKeyLoadError` implements `APIStatus`\n250:   - File: `pkg/router/errors_test.go`\n251:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTError -v`\n252: \n253: - [ ] **T7.3**: Add middleware tests in `middleware_test.go`\n254:   - Test `JWTAuthMiddleware` with valid token\n255:   - Test `JWTAuthMiddleware` with invalid token\n256:   - Test `JWTAuthMiddleware` with missing token\n257:   - Test `JWTAuthMiddleware` with expired token\n258:   - Test `JWTAuthMiddleware` skip paths\n259:   - Test `DefaultTokenExtractor` Bearer format\n260:   - Test `DefaultTokenExtractor` missing header\n261:   - Test `DefaultTokenExtractor` invalid format\n262:   - Test `GetClaimsFromContext` extraction\n263:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware_test.go`\n264:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTAuth -v`\n265: \n266: - [ ] **T7.4**: Add KeyManager tests in `jwt_test.go`\n267:   - Test `NewKeyManager` constructor\n268:   - Test `KeyManager.Exists` with mock client\n269:   - Test `KeyManager.Load` with mock secret\n270:   - Test `KeyManager.Store` with mock client\n271:   - Test `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret` integration\n272:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n273:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManager -v`\n274: \n275: ### Phase 8: Integration & Coverage (ST-8)\n276: \n277: - [ ] **T8.1**: Integration test for full JWT flow\n278:   - Generate token → Validate token → Extract claims\n279:   - Verify claims match original input\n280:   - File: `pkg/router/jwt_test.go`\n281:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTIntegration -v`\n282: \n283: - [ ] **T8.2**: Integration test for middleware chain\n284:   - Request → JWTAuthMiddleware → Handler with claims access\n285:   - Verify 401 on invalid token\n286:   - Verify 200 with claims injection on valid token\n287:   - File: `pkg/router/middleware_test.go`\n288:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -run TestMiddlewareIntegration -v`\n289: \n290: - [ ] **T8.3**: Verify test coverage ≥ 80%\n291:   - Run `go test ./pkg/router -cover`\n292:   - Identify uncovered code paths\n293:   - Add missing test cases\n294:   - File: `pkg/router/*_test.go`\n295:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -cover`\n296: \n297: - [ ] **T8.4**: All router tests pass\n298:   - `go test ./pkg/router -v`\n299:   - Fix any failing tests\n300:   - File: `pkg/router/*_test.go`\n301:   - Verification: `go test ./pkg/router -v`\n302: \n303: ---\n304: \n305: ## Task Dependencies\n306: \n307: ```\n308: Phase 1 (Completed)\n309:   T1.1 ── T1.2 ── T1.3\n310:      │\n311:      ▼\n312: Phase 2 (Completed)\n313:   T2.1 ── T2.2 ── T2.3 ── T2.4 ── T2.5\n314:      │\n315:      ▼\n316: Phase 3 (JWT Verification)\n317:   T3.1 ── T3.2 ──┬── T3.3 ── T3.4\n318:                 │\n319: Phase 4 (Middleware) ────────────────────────────┘\n320:   T4.1 ── T4.2 ── T4.3 ── T4.4 ── T4.5 ── T4.6\n321:      │\n322:      ▼\n323: Phase 5 (Key Persistence)\n324:   T5.1 ── T5.2 ── T5.3 ── T5.4 ── T5.5 ── T5.6 ── T5.7\n325:      │\n326:      ▼\n327: Phase 6 (JWT Config - Optional)\n328:   T6.1 ── T6.2 ── T6.3\n329:      │\n330:      ▼\n331: Phase 7 (Unit Tests)\n332:   T7.1 ── T7.2 ── T7.3 ── T7.4\n333:      │\n334:      ▼\n335: Phase 8 (Integration & Coverage)\n336:   T8.1 ── T8.2 ── T8.3 ── T8.4\n337: ```\n338: \n339: ---\n340: \n341: ## Verification Commands\n342: \n343: | Task | Verification Command |\n344: |------|----------------------|\n345: | T1.1, T1.2 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewJWTManager -v` |\n346: | T1.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTSigningError -v` |\n347: | T2.1, T2.2 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerGenerateToken -v` |\n348: | T2.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestEncodePrivateKeyPEM -v` |\n349: | T2.4 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerGetPublicKey -v` |\n350: | T3.1 | `go build ./pkg/router/...` |\n351: | T3.2 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTError -v` |\n352: | T3.3, T3.4 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerValidateToken -v` |\n353: | T4.1, T4.2 | `go build ./pkg/router/...` |\n354: | T4.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestDefaultTokenExtractor -v` |\n355: | T4.4, T4.5, T4.6 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTAuthMiddleware -v` |\n356: | T5.1, T5.2, T5.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestNewKeyManager -v` |\n357: | T5.4 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManagerExists -v` |\n358: | T5.5 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManagerLoad -v` |\n359: | T5.6 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManagerStore -v` |\n360: | T5.7 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerKeyPersistence -v` |\n361: | T6.1 | `go build ./pkg/router/...` |\n362: | T6.2, T6.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTConfig -v` |\n363: | T7.1 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTManagerValidateToken -v` |\n364: | T7.2 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTError -v` |\n365: | T7.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTAuth -v` |\n366: | T7.4 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestKeyManager -v` |\n367: | T8.1 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestJWTIntegration -v` |\n368: | T8.2 | `go test ./pkg/router -run TestMiddlewareIntegration -v` |\n369: | T8.3 | `go test ./pkg/router -cover` |\n370: | T8.4 | `go test ./pkg/router -v` |\n371: \n372: ---\n373: \n374: ## Acceptance Criteria\n375: \n376: - [ ] JWT Token 签发功能正常 (T2.1-T2.4 completed)\n377: - [ ] `ValidateToken` 方法正确验证 Token (T3.3)\n378: - [ ] JWT 错误类型完整定义 (T3.2)\n379: - [ ] Token 验证中间件正确拦截无效请求 (T4.4)\n380: - [ ] 跳过路径配置正常工作 (T4.1, T4.4)\n381: - [ ] Claims 正确注入到 Context (T4.6)\n382: - [ ] Kubernetes Secret 密钥持久化正常 (T5.3-T5.7)\n383: - [ ] 密钥加载与存储正常 (T5.4-T5.6)\n384: - [ ] 支持 RS256 算法 (已有)\n385: - [ ] 测试覆盖率 ≥ 80% (T8.3)\n386: - [ ] 所有验证命令通过 (T8.4)\n387: \n388: ---\n389: \n390: ## Files Modified/Created\n391: \n392: | File | Status | Description |\n393: |------|--------|-------------|\n394: | `pkg/router/jwt.go` | Modified | Add ValidateToken, RouterClaims, KeyManager, JWTConfig |\n395: | `pkg/router/jwt_test.go` | Modified | Add validation, KeyManager, integration tests |\n396: | `pkg/router/errors.go` | Modified | Add JWT error types (ValidationError, ExpiredError, etc.) |\n397: | `pkg/router/errors_test.go` | Modified | Add JWT error type tests |\n398: | `pkg/router/middleware.go` | Modified | Add JWTAuthMiddleware, TokenExtractor |\n399: | `pkg/router/middleware_test.go` | Modified | Add JWT middleware tests |\n400: | `pkg/router/doc.go` | Modified | Add JWTManagerInterface updates if needed |\n401: \n402: ---\n403: \n404: ## Notes\n405: \n406: - **Design completed at Stage ST-3**\n407: - **Phase 1-2 (ST-1, ST-2) already implemented**\n408: - **Dependencies**:\n409:   - `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` - JWT signing and parsing (already used)\n410:   - `crypto/rsa` - RSA key operations (already used)\n411:   - `crypto/x509` - Key serialization (already used)\n412:   - `encoding/pem` - PEM encoding (already used)\n413:   - `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` - Kubernetes Secret persistence (optional)\n414:   - `k8s.io/klog/v2` - Logging (already used)\n415: - **Environment Variables**:\n416:   - `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (optional, default \"default\") - Router identity namespace\n417: - **Security Notes**:\n418:   - RS256 preferred for asymmetric verification\n419:   - Private key stored in Kubernetes Secret (base64 encoded)\n420:   - Token expiration: 5 minutes (short-lived)\n421:   - Key rotation: future enhancement\n422: \n423: ---\n424: \n425: ## Implementation Timeline\n426: \n427: | Phase | Tasks | Status | Completion |\n428: |-------|-------|--------|------------|\n429: | Phase 1: Core Data Structures | T1.1-T1.3 | Completed | 100% |\n430: | Phase 2: JWT Generation | T2.1-T2.5 | Completed | 100% |\n431: | Phase 3: JWT Verification | T3.1-T3.4 | Not Started | 0% |\n432: | Phase 4: Authentication Middleware | T4.1-T4.6 | Not Started | 0% |\n433: | Phase 5: Key Persistence | T5.1-T5.7 | Not Started | 0% |\n434: | Phase 6: JWT Config (Optional) | T6.1-T6.3 | Not Started | 0% |\n435: | Phase 7: Unit Tests | T7.1-T7.4 | Not Started | 0% |\n436: | Phase 8: Integration & Coverage | T8.1-T8.4 | Not Started | 0% |\n437: \n438: **Total Progress: 25% Complete (8/32 tasks)**\n\n(End of file - total 438 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-011 — Router JWT 认证与签发 |\n| Module | `pkg/router` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Core Data Structures (ST-1) ✓\n\n- [x] **T1.1**: Define JWT constants in `jwt.go`\n  - `rsaKeySize = 2048`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-011/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775853608457,"end":1775853608513}}}}
